(1) Necessary team created files: (all of these files should be copied to /usr/local/bin)
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
| Filename		   | Modification Notes						|
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
| ValidateUSB_Hover.jar    |								|
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
| Xmodmap_orig		   |								|
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
| Xmodmap_restricted 	   |								|
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
| usb_add.sh		   | Replace all instances of "username" with your username	|
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

(2) Obtain the latest stable version of the Linux Kernel from https://www.kernel.org (version used for project: 3.19.x)

(3) Overwrite the following files with the delivered files (found at cse_825/Project/drive_modification/source) at the specificed location (where linux-3.19 is the root of the Linux kernel code): /linux-3.19/drivers/hid/usbhid
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
| Filename		   | Modification Notes														|
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
| Makefile		   | Added Makefile targets that build the USBHID drivers for the most recent kernel release					|
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
| hid-core.c		   | Added code to the usbhid_start function to call the usb_add shell script (and added unrecognized hid.h header information)	|
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
*let me know if this doesn't work - there may be more files with unrecognized information from hid.h*

(4) Execute the "make" command from the usbhid directory

(5) From /lib/modules/$(uname -r)/kernel/drivers/hid/usbhid, excute the following command: sudo rmmod usbhid.ko

(6) Copy the usbhid.ko file to /lib/modules/$(uname -r)/kernel/drivers/hid/usbhid
    Note: you can overwrite the usbhid.ko file currently located at that location, but the suggestion is to save the original ko file under a different name and then move this file to the specified directory

(7) From /lib/modules/$(uname -r)/kernel/drivers/hid/usbhid, excute the following command: sudo insmod usbhid.ko

(8) To confirm module installation, you can execute "lsmod" and check that the usbhid Module has a size of 52783

